The paper deals with image smoothing using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of unsupervised learning is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses edge-preserving regularizers, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents results for various image manipulation tasks, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
